<h2 class="main">Enclosure</h2>
<h3 class="sub">Invoice to Richard Washington</h3>

<div class="docbody">
<div class="opener">
<table class="salutationBlock">
        <tr>
		<td class="salutationRight">Fort Loudoun 15th April 1757</td>
	      </tr>
      </table>
</div>
<p>Invoice of Sundry Goods to be Shipd by Mr Richd Washington of London for the use of G. Washington viz.<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-02-04-02-0075-0002-fn-0001" id="GEWN-02-04-02-0075-0002-fn-0001-ptr">1</a></p>

<p style="text-indent: 0;">A Marble Chimney piece of the Dimensions of the Inclosd (given by the Workmen) the Cost not to exceed 15 Guineas.</p>
<p style="text-align: center; text-indent: 0;">N.B. let it be carefully packd.</p>
   <p style="text-indent: 0;">A Neat Landskip 3 feet by 21 Inches1 Inch Margin for a Chimy.</p>
   <p style="text-indent: 0;">250 panes window Glass 11 by 9.</p>
   <p style="text-indent: 0;">Paper for 5 Rooms of the following Dimensions (viz.) 18 by 12 16 by 12. 16 by 14. 18 by 15. and 15 by 16 all 8 feet pitch<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-02-04-02-0075-0002-fn-0002" id="GEWN-02-04-02-0075-0002-fn-0002-ptr">2</a> the Paper differing in their Coloursalso paper of a very good kind and colour for a Dining Room 18 by 16 above the Chair boards the pitch of the Room is 11 Feet.</p>
   <p style="text-indent: 0;">Papier Machee for the Ceiling of two Rooms, one of them 18 Feet Square, the other 18 by 16 with C[orne]r Chimneys.</p>
   <p style="text-indent: 0;">Two neat Mahagony Tables 4 feet square when spread and to join occasionally.</p>
   <p style="text-indent: 0;">1 Dozn neat and strong Mahagony Chairs at 21/.</p>
   <p style="text-indent: 0;">1 Dozn fashionable Locks for Partition doors &amp; appurtenances.</p>
   <p style="text-indent: 0;">1 dozn fashe Hinges for the said Doors &amp; 2 pr larger.</p>

<div class="closer">
<p class="signed">Go: Washington</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="docback">
<span class="pb center" title="page number in print edition (no page scan available)" id="GEWN-02-04-02-pb-0135">[135]</span>
<div class="note-source" id="GEWN-02-04-02-0075-0002-sn">

   <p>
<abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Letter Book Copy: letters copied into a bound letter-book ]">LB</abbr>, <span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ U.S. Library of Congress, George Washington Papers, Washington, D.C. ]">DLC:GW</span>.
 The letter-book copy is in GWs hand.</p>

</div>
<div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-04-02-0075-0002-fn-0001-ptr" id="GEWN-02-04-02-0075-0002-fn-0001">1</a>

   <p>For a description of the items sent and their price, see <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-05-02-0031" class="document">Richard Washingtons Invoice, 10 Nov. 1757</a><span class="choice deletion" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover_choice ] header=[]  body=[ Deleted: ', printed below' &lt;span style='font-size: 90%'&gt;[[2014-11-06]]&lt;/span&gt; ]"><img alt="deletion" src="images/deletion_mark-trans.png" style="border:none;vertical-align: text-bottom; padding-right:2px"/></span>.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-04-02-0075-0002-fn-0002-ptr" id="GEWN-02-04-02-0075-0002-fn-0002">2</a>

   <p>GW was using the term pitch to mean height.</p>

